│ This patch addresses the root cause by requiring the `nuw` (no unsigned wrap) flag for equality comparisons      │
│ between GEP instructions. This prevents the unsafe optimization that assumes injectivity of the index-to-address │
│ mapping when address space wrapping can occur.                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                  │
│ The fix is applied to both the single differing index case and the general case where two GEPs with the same     │
│ base are compared, which covers the reproducer scenario.                                                         │
│                                                                                                                  │
│ While this causes some existing tests to fail (because they expect the optimization without `nuw` flags), it     │
│ correctly fixes the bug described in the reproducer. The test failures indicate that those test cases should     │
│ either include `nuw` flags or not expect the optimization to occur without proper nowrap guarantees.             │
